# Initialize python environment
## why?
This will avoid conflict with the installed dependencies between all the projects.

## how?
1. open a bash terminal in vscode
2. create the environment: run python -m venv env
3. activate the environment: source env/Scripts/activate

you can deactivate with: deactivate

## Installing dependencies
run command: pip install -r requirements.txt

# Setting project .env
check in .env.example the required variables an set them in .env or .env.*
